1. to change mint system font : settings ->
========
chrome://settings/fonts
Standard font and size. Default: (Times New Roman) on Windows.
Serif font. Default (Times New Roman) on Windows.
Sans-serif font. Default (Arial) on Windows.
Fixed-width font. Default (Consolas) on Windows.
Minimum font size. Default Tiny on Windows.
=========
1. lower-resolution displays, sans-serifs tend to display better
2. higher-resolution displays can better handle the fine details of serifs
3. I predict weâ€™ll see serif typefaces used more on the web in the coming years.
